---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Meteorology — Weather Terms That Score Big"
  description="Meteorology and weather words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. VORTEX (16pts), CYCLONE (14pts), GUST (5pts). Weather vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble meteorology words, weather scrabble terms, vortex scrabble points, cyclone scrabble, gust scrabble word, meteorology vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Meteorology — Weather Terms That Score Big","description":"Meteorology and weather words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. VORTEX (16pts), CYCLONE (14pts), GUST (5pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-meteorology"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is VORTEX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! VORTEX scores 16 points (V=4, O=1, R=1, T=1, E=1, X=8). It's a spinning mass of air or fluid. The X tile (8pts) and V tile (4pts) together contribute 12 of the 16 total points, making it one of the best X words available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is CYCLONE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CYCLONE scores 14 points (C=3, Y=4, C=3, L=1, O=1, N=1, E=1). It's a large-scale rotating weather system. Two C tiles (3pts each) plus Y (4pts) provide 10 of the 14 points. At 7 letters, it's a bingo candidate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is GUST valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. GUST scores 5 points (G=2, U=1, S=1, T=1). It means a brief strong rush of wind. While low-scoring alone, GUST is useful as a 4-letter gap filler and hooks to GUSTS (6pts), GUSTY (9pts), and GUSTING (9pts)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Meteorology — Weather Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Weather and meteorology terms pack serious scoring power in Scrabble. VORTEX delivers 16 points with its X tile, CYCLONE uses double-C and Y for 14, and even short words like GUST provide tactical value on tight boards. These are words everyone recognises from weather forecasts — no memorisation needed.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">VORTEX (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CYCLONE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TYPHOON</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GUST</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Weather Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">VORTEX — 16 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">V=4, O=1, R=1, T=1, E=1, X=8 · 6 letters · V+X combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A spinning column of air or fluid, like a tornado's core. VORTEX combines V (4pts) and X (8pts) in a single 6-letter word — that's 12 points from just two tiles. On a DWS, this word scores 32 points base.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌀 CYCLONE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · C=3, Y=4, C=3, L=1, O=1, N=1, E=1 · Storm system</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌊 TYPHOON</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · T=1, Y=4, P=3, H=4, O=1, O=1, N=1 · Pacific storm</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💨 GUST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · G=2, U=1, S=1, T=1 · Wind burst</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⛈️ SQUALL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · S=1, Q=10, U=1, A=1, L=1, L=1 · Sudden storm</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Weather Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BLIZZARD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">20pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLEET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONSOON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HAIL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOGGY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Weather Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">VORTEX burns V and X together:</span> Both V (4pts) and X (8pts) are hard to place individually. VORTEX uses both in one natural word. Place the X on a DLS for 24+ points from a single 6-letter play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CYCLONE is a 7-letter bingo:</span> At exactly 7 tiles, CYCLONE earns the 50-point bonus. With double-C and Y, you're looking at 64 total points. Hold C, Y, C, L, O, N, E for this powerhouse.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SQUALL dumps Q with U:</span> At 15 points, SQUALL is a strong Q dump using common letters (S, A, L, L). The double-L ending connects easily to existing board words.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Meteorology covers <span class="text-white font-medium">four premium tiles</span> — X (VORTEX), Q (SQUALL), V (VORTEX), and Y (CYCLONE/TYPHOON). No other single category gives you reliable plays for this many high-value tiles simultaneously.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy-planets/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy Planets</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-chemistry-elements/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Chemistry Elements</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-electricity/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Electricity</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-weather/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Weather</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Nature Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid weather term instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
